Thick cut of beef steak
Beef Bouillon(s)
1 Stick of Butter

Mix cube with a bit of hot butter until a paste is formed. Heavily salt steak for 60 minutes with kosher salt. Rince in sink and pat complely dry. Rub paste into the meat and let stand for 60 minutes. To a very hot skillet, add meat and tilt pan so to create a well for the butter. With a large spoon, laddle hot butter over steak constantly until desired readiness. Let sit for 10 minutes before serving.

